  "texts": [
    "By demonstrating that subjective norms play a significant role in shaping purchase intention, this study highlights the importance of social influence and normative considerations in the context of sustainable consumption.",
    "These findings contribute to the validation and further development of the NAT.",
    "Value for research on environmental accidents: This study provides a theoretical foundation for studying environmental accidents by identifying specific dimensions that can be used to measure their impact on consumer behavior.",
    "The conceptualization of these dimensions can guide future research in examining the effects of different types of environmental accidents on various consumer behaviors, beyond the context of green apparel.",
    "In conclusion, the theoretical implications of this study are noteworthy as they integrate two established theories, introduce environmental accidents as variables, validate the NAT, and provide a foundation for studying the impact of environmental accidents on consumer behavior."
